At the time of the riots, queer people in Canada, America, the UK, and indeed much of the Western world still faced systematic, state-sponsored violence, including medical violence, propaganda campaigns against their identities, imprisonment, and more. In 2024, there are still over 60 countries in which queer people can be jailed or much worse for our identities, and even in more progressive countries, bigotry and hate remains rampant. but love will always be stronger than hate. this is why we celebrate pride: to celebrate love, for ourselves and for our community, no matter where in the world they are. to remember those that blazed the trails that have gotten us to where we are today. to remember that nobody is free until everybody is free. happy pride month, y'all!!
